## Dictionary Definition

Domain - a particular field of thought, activity, or interest, especially one over which someone has control, influence, or rights.

[Collins Dictionary](https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/domain)

This definition is very applicable to that applicable to the HMPPS Digital Strategy for prisons. A team implementing a digital domain creates all components necessary to manage, maintain and control data within that domain.

## HMPPS Digital Definition

For a set of “things”, a Domain describes the data, the technical services, and the teams supporting those. These “things” are normally entities that relate to real-world concepts such as “Person”, “Risks”, “Pay”.

